thing is functioning properly without unexpected issues!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing child loader functions**\\n\\nI need to test the child loader's `isReady` function first, then check `getModuleHMAC`. This process covers both options, even if the system is already ready. It seems like I’ll have to use reflection again to effectively achieve this. It’s a bit tricky, but I think I can manage it. I'll make sure to document everything I find during this testing phase to keep track of my progress and any issues that arise.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dAA211GZvkV3QFHEzi9TfkvM|fc_0cf9765528958da8016a3f7533b934819388b0227f6facf16d", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/FipsStatusTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bc_fips;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertArrayEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLConnection;\nimport java.net.URLStreamHandler;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class FipsStatusTest {\n    private static final String FIPS_STATUS_CLASS_NAME = \"org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus\";\n    private static final String NATIVE_CPU_VARIANT_PROPERTY = \"org.bouncycastle.native.cpu_variant\";\n    private static final String MARKER_RESOURCE_NAME = \"org/bouncycastle/MARKER\";\n\n    @BeforeAll\n    static void useJavaOnlyNativeVariant() {\n        System.setProperty(NATIVE_CPU_VARIANT_PROPERTY, \"java\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void publicStatusApiInitializesModuleAndReportsReady() {\n        assertTrue(FipsStatus.isReady());\n        assertEquals(FipsStatus.READY, FipsStatus.getStatusMessage());\n        assertEquals(32, FipsStatus.getModuleHMAC().length);\n        assertTrue(FipsStatus.isReady());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void isolatedStatusUsesMarkerResourceWhenCodeSourceIsUnavailable() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            MarkerFallbackClassLoader classLoader = new MarkerFallbackClassLoader(\n                    FipsStatusTest.class.getClassLoader());\n            Class<?> statusClass = classLoader.loadClass(FIPS_STATUS_CLASS_NAME);\n\n            assertEquals(Boolean.TRUE, statusClass.getMethod(\"isReady\").invoke(null));\n            assertArrayEquals(new byte[32], (byte[])statusClass.getMethod(\"getModuleHMAC\").invoke(null));\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            handleInvocationFailure(exception);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void handleInvocationFailure(InvocationTargetException exception) throws Exception {\n        Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n        if (cause instanceof Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n            return;\n        }\n        if (cause instanceof Exception checkedException) {\n            throw checkedException;\n        }\n        throw exception;\n    }\n\n    private static final class MarkerFallbackClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final ClassLoader resourceLoader;\n\n        MarkerFallbackClassLoader(ClassLoader resourceLoader) {\n            super(null);\n            this.resourceLoader = resourceLoader;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = loadClassFromBouncyCastleJar(name);\n                }\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader().loadClass(name);\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL getResource(String name) {\n            if (MARKER_RESOURCE_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return markerUrl();\n            }\n            return resourceLoader.getResource(name);\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> loadClassFromBouncyCastleJar(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!name.startsWith(\"org.bouncycastle.\")) {\n                return null;\n            }\n            return findClass(name);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            String resourceName = name.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream input = resourceLoader.getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n                if (input == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n                }\n                byte[] bytecode = input.readAllBytes();\n                return defineClass(name, bytecode, 0, bytecode.length);\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name, exception);\n            }\n        }\n\n        private URL markerUrl() {\n            try {\n                return new URL(null, \"vfs:/bc-fips/MARKER\", new URLStreamHandler() {\n                    @Override\n                    protected URLConnection openConnection(URL url) throws IOException {\n                        throw new IOException(\"marker URL is only used for its external form\");\n                    }\n                });\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new IllegalStateException(exception);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8091, "output": 3787, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35430, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782543631459, "responseId": "resp_0cf9765528958da8016a3f75100980819380478945ac0f5d35"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_dAA211GZvkV3QFHEzi9TfkvM|fc_0cf9765528958da8016a3f7533b934819388b0227f6facf16d", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 5414 bytes to tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/FipsStatusTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782543676857}]}
