[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering ClassUtilTest issues**\n\nI'm thinking about whether I could disable ClassUtilTest. I guess the answer is no. It seems like ClassUtil tests might not have initialized FipsStatus under instrumentation, since BouncyCastleFipsProvider's Service.newInstance does. However, I'm wondering if Cipher.getInstance(String, Provider) actually uses the service when the provider object isn't registered. It did pass, so then maybe it does use it? I'm a bit unclear here.\n\n**Investigating ClassUtil initialization**\n\nI think it’s time for a ClassUtil self-test. It seems like it’s initialized, but the dynamic report being false suggests that the class order might not be the cause. If ClassUtil runs first, then it should cover Class.forName, right? But what if FipsStatus is initialized before the agent starts? I wonder if the bc-fips provider's static initialization might be influencing this. I’ll have to inspect the console and check the test method orders. What about the native test XML?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cf9765528958da8016a3f75d296e48193baca54661fd39e0c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP3Xg0ebGwgYibZbjcNjDz6vkOGTm9K_t8ASBfUWWXUfIp5exQ-dIqPMdXOoghUZsUYJQWTq5jmkfpvCAI2bHOcpPuCWGdTA1LolXBvCQP2yF9SklvgEH12i_cMXuCy4pyvQn6Jb-t8933sPIvlZrIXRYloLJ6AbO-ZhX9tL2vIud1kswMUZzJV18j4LMbOGFfciGV5w1yZa7lPtYCm7JzWeqoyPegn12d_l_TO-VwwhDITrD4uC4QgL3mwx7AOBUQ6SARxPhlhtSYcWIuhgpOT_7s6g7cmD3ZiXPf4oV_aVHH0b_FN0uNUL1pNCF4IIy7jJjV138o9gFE_4IPoEqVvhAh5PuExSSIPbukWNQNNREVrbMjPsvcxpoJtEKA9wCenVGDlzQ08dC7MILk5c0YoSqi5SmD4L8VFzJcTQuB3MgT550CjoTriYAMhYQnTCcLP12MPnj489lfn6A9wtWILeQauL9l5EtcqIvRL-nL7fMJbMjhDfGOjn7KM_voj2pMUUQFPF5A68yRmkVTiPeqFDAHs2pBQWUN_P6IOndRON5jWdqo88T6hHKR4dxi138GTUlvQJIgo0sHC78Sj0Hl6L8eytghO27Vtal28AMTN3Vu8d5k5sdCzSXRz4gHmmBcAc0Mk5fT-QDNB7rx1d6VbstQVZ9cK23cDTjVo8jd6UYFMMrCKp2_Oa1U7P2QJTubMe6PxRF3prynr--PItXtKqTxiI