[assistant] Updated the active-class coverage attempt for `org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes made:
[assistant] - Refined `FipsStatusTest.java`
[assistant]   - Keeps a dedicated one-to-one test file for `FipsStatus`.
[assistant]   - Forces the test class to run before other test classes with `@Order(1)`, so `FipsStatus.isReady()` can reach first-time initialization and the `Class.forName(...)` call in `FipsStatus.loadClass`.
[assistant]   - Refined the isolated class loader so `FipsStatus` is defined with the bc-fips `CodeSource`, while `LICENSE` is defined with a null `CodeSource`. This is intended to drive the public API into the marker-resource fallback and reach `ClassLoader#getResource(...)` in `FipsStatus.getMarker`.
[assistant]   - Added bounded Native Image fallback behavior when class-byte resources are unavailable in the native executable.
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Added:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/resources/junit-platform.properties`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests, per instruction.
