[assistant] Implemented another active-class-focused refinement for `org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes:
[assistant] - Updated `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/build.gradle`
[assistant]   - Forces `org.bouncycastle.native.cpu_variant=java` for JVM tests, native runtime, and native-image build.
[assistant]   - Adds `--initialize-at-run-time=org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus` so Native Image runtime execution can reach first-time `FipsStatus.isReady()` initialization and the `Class.forName(...)` call site instead of inheriting build-time initialized state.
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Refined `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/FipsStatusTest.java`
[assistant]   - Orders FipsStatus tests so active-class initialization runs first.
[assistant]   - Adds a direct public API initialization test for the self-test path.
[assistant]   - Adds a module HMAC lookup test.
[assistant]   - Keeps the isolated class-loader marker fallback test, with safer handling for Native Image and checksum-failure layouts.
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Added/kept:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/resources/junit-platform.properties`
[assistant]   - Ensures JUnit honors class ordering so `FipsStatusTest` runs before other bc-fips tests can initialize `FipsStatus`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests, per instruction.
[assistant-event] text_end
